The paper deals with the performance of maximum ratio combining (MRC) in the presence of interference, which is a common problem in wireless communication systems. This makes cs.IT (Information Theory) the most likely category, as it deals with the fundamental limits of communication systems. The paper also involves modeling the interference field as a Poisson point process, which is a common technique in network analysis, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another likely category. The paper also deals with spatial correlation, which is a common problem in signal processing, making cs.SI (Signal Processing) a likely category. The paper also involves studying the diversity behavior of MRC, which is a common problem in wireless communication systems, making cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves deriving exact distributions and upper and lower bounds, which is a common problem in probability and statistics, making cs.PF (Probability) a possible category.
